# Wallpaper Setup Guide for Sway

## Methods to Set Wallpaper

### Method 1: Single Image (Quickest)

Edit `~/.config/sway/config.d/output`:

```bash
# Set same wallpaper on all monitors
output * bg ~/Pictures/wallpaper.jpg fill
```

### Method 2: Different Wallpaper Per Monitor

```bash
# Laptop display
output eDP-1 bg ~/Pictures/laptop_wallpaper.jpg fill

# External monitor
output HDMI-A-1 bg ~/Pictures/monitor_wallpaper.jpg fill
```

### Method 3: Random Wallpaper at Startup

Add to `~/.config/sway/config.d/autostart`:

```bash
# Random wallpaper from directory
exec_always find ~/Pictures/Wallpapers -type f | shuf -n 1 | xargs swaymsg output '*' bg
```

### Method 4: Using swaybg (Recommended for Advanced Control)

```bash
# Install swaybg (if not installed)
sudo dnf install swaybg

# Basic usage
swaymsg output '*' bg ~/Pictures/wallpaper.jpg fill

# Different modes:
# fill    - Scale to cover (default)
# stretch - Stretch to fit
# fit     - Scale to fit (may have bars)
# center  - Center without scaling
# tile    - Tile/repeat image
```

